## Student Data Analysis

When working with grade or assessment data:

**What to produce:**
- Class averages and distributions (how many students at each performance level)
- Individual student trends over time
- Standards mastery breakdown (which standards the class is strong/weak on)
- Comparison across class periods or sections
- Lists of students who need intervention or enrichment

**Visualization:**
- Bar charts for class distributions
- Line charts for individual student trends over time
- Heat maps for standards mastery across the class
- Keep it simple — the teacher needs to act on this, not present it at a conference

**Practical output:**
- Groups for targeted instruction (based on data, not alphabetical)
- Re-teaching priorities (which standards to revisit)
- Students to watch (declining trends, inconsistent performance)
- Celebration list (students showing growth)

